  "lessonText": "The Code Builder provides an interactive environment to practice HTML coding.",
  "data": {
    "content": "The Code Builder is a tool that allows you to write and execute HTML code directly in your browser.\n\n*   It provides real-time feedback, helping you understand how your code changes affect the output.\n*   You can experiment with different HTML elements and attributes, such as the `<video>` element discussed earlier, to see how they work.\n*   It's a great way to reinforce your understanding of HTML foundations and semantics.\n*   Use it to practice embedding videos using the `<video>` element, similar to what you learned in the HTML5 Video Element Explained video.\n*   Remember the basic attributes like `src` for specifying the video source, as in `<source src=\"sample video.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">`."
